How To properly package a boot.img for MTD support on Epic 4G (SPH-D700).

1 - Build a kernel using the included stage1 initramfs (initramfs_stage1).
2 - Copy the zImage to your working directory.

For CM7 / MIUI:
3 - Make any desired changes to the initramfs files in initramfs_cm7.
4 - Run the create_boot.img.sh script with the cm arg.
    "./create_boot.img.sh cm"

For TouchWiz:
3 - Make any desired changes to the initramfs files in initramfs_tw.
4 - Run the create_boot.img.sh script with the tw arg.
    "./create_boot.img.sh tw"

5 - Create a flashable zip to install the newly created boot.img.
